<P>CAUSES. The <HI>remote</HI> or <HI>inducing</HI> are, bad nur&s;ing&mdash;&s;uck|ling children too long&mdash;an acid produced from the milk with which the child is fed for the fir&s;t nine months, or feeding <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> on unfermented ferinaceous &s;ub&s;tances, and indulging too much in their u&s;e, particularly &s;uch aliments as po&s;&s;e&s;s too firm a <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">, are too vi&s;cid and &s;our, as bread not well fermented, chee&s;e-cakes,
